---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import ServiceCTA from '../../components/ServiceCTA.astro';

const schemaData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  "serviceType": "Custom Metal Railings",
  "provider": {
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "name": "Urban Forge"
  },
  "areaServed": "New York City",
  "description": "Custom metal railings, cable railings, and wrought iron railings in New York. Code-compliant and expertly designed."
};
---

<Layout title="Custom Metal Railings New York | Urban Forge">
  <Header />
  
  <main class="container service-detail">
    <div class="breadcrumb">
      <a href="/services">Services</a> &gt; <span>Custom Metal Railings</span>
    </div>
    
    <h1>Custom Metal Railings in New York</h1>
    
    <img src="/images/custom_railings.png" alt="Custom Metal Railings New York" class="hero-image" />
    
    <div class="content-body">
      <h2>Expert Metal Railing Fabrication & Installation</h2>
      <p>Whether you need sleek, modern stainless steel cable railings for an outdoor roof deck or hand-forged wrought iron railings to preserve the historic character of a Brooklyn Heights townhouse, Urban Forge delivers unmatched architectural quality. We handle every step of the process—from engineering calculations and material selection to precision fabrication and white-glove installation. Our team works hand-in-hand with luxury architects, designers, and homebuilders to bring custom railing systems to life.</p>
      
      <h3>Our Custom Railing Profiles</h3>
      <p>We work with a wide range of structural and decorative alloys, tailoring the metallurgy to match your interior design scheme or outdoor exposure demands:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Modern Cable Railing Systems:</strong> Utilizing marine-grade T316 stainless steel cable infills and slim steel posts for a minimalist look that preserves panoramic city and landscape views.</li>
        <li><strong>Hand-Forged Wrought Iron:</strong> Forged by hand on traditional anvils. We create custom scrolls, pickets, collars, and finials that match the historical architectural contexts of brownstones and estates.</li>
        <li><strong>Luxury Brass & Bronze:</strong> Living alloys polished to a mirror finish or treated with statuary chemical patinas. They naturally tarnish and develop rich character under high traffic.</li>
        <li><strong>Industrial Steel & Pipe Railings:</strong> Heavy-duty profiles suited for commercial lofts, industrial fire escapes, and utilitarian spaces requiring structural resilience.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3>Strict NYC Building Code Compliance</h3>
      <p>Designing guardrails and handrails in New York City requires absolute familiarity with local building departments. Our engineering team ensures every project meets or exceeds the following safety codes:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Height Standards:</strong> Guardrails must stand at least 42 inches tall from the finished floor level, while handrails must be consistently mounted between 34 and 38 inches from the stair tread nosing.</li>
        <li><strong>The 4-Inch Sphere Rule:</strong> Pickets and cables must be tensioned and spaced close enough together so that a 4-inch diameter sphere cannot pass through any point of the infill, preventing safety hazards.</li>
        <li><strong>Structural Load Requirements:</strong> All guardrails must withstand a concentrated load of 200 pounds applied in any direction at the top rail, or a uniform load of 50 pounds per linear foot.</li>
      </ol>
      
      <h3>The Art of Surface Finishes</h3>
      <p>To ensure your custom railings remain beautiful for decades, we apply specialized coatings. For exterior railings exposed to rain and coastal environments, we execute a multi-step rust prevention treatment, including hot-dip galvanizing or zinc-rich primers, followed by high-durability electrostatic powder coating. For interior commissions, we specialize in oil-rubbed bronze finishes, hand-applied beeswax coatings, and unlacquered satins that preserve the metallic sheen.</p>

      <ServiceCTA title="Ready to start your railing project?" buttonText="Request a Quote" />
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <!-- Service Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schemaData)} />
</Layout>

<style>
  .service-detail {
    padding-block: var(--spacing-xl);
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }
  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--color-brushed-brass);
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    color: var(--color-matte-black);
  }
  .hero-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
    border: 2px solid var(--color-brushed-brass);
  }
  .content-body h2, .content-body h3 {
    color: var(--color-matte-black);
    margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  .content-body p, .content-body ul, .content-body ol {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #444;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  }
  .content-body ul, .content-body ol {
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  .content-body li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
